import React,{useState} from 'react' function LoginPage({handleLogin,onLoginSuccess}) { const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState('login'); const [loginData, setLoginData] = useState({ email: '', password: '' }); const [view,changeview]=useState("login") return (
handleLogin(e,loginData)}>
setLoginData({...loginData, email: e.target.value})} placeholder="Email" />
setLoginData({...loginData, password: e.target.value})} placeholder="Password" />
) } export default LoginPage
